  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cholera Prevention and Response in the North through the Haitian Red Cross</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Community meetings
- Training of community volunteers in Epidemics Control and interpersonal communication 
- Community sensitization sessions
- Intensive hygiene promotion in communities during cholera outbreaks target towards cholera affected communities.
- Distribution of hygiene products in community during cholera outbreaks and at large public events (traditional festivities, carnivals, etc.) and specific days (Hand Washing Day)
- Installation of hand washing stations for large public events.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will contribute to the elimination of cholera for the three departments in the North of Haiti during the next 12 months through sensitization campaign and hygiene product distribution, and will support the Haitian Ministry of Health in the Coordination of Cholera Related activities across the Red Cross Movement in Haiti.</narrative>
  </description>
